<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12147h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12147h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12147h"> 147(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Victor</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans le proc&egrave;s de canonisation les allusions sont tr&egrave;s vagues; mais voici dans le m&ecirc;me ordre d&apos;id&eacute;es un compliment que Gerson adresse au ma&icirc;tre: &ldquo;Je me figure que vous &ecirc;tes l&apos;ange de l&apos;Apocalypse dont le proph&egrave;te de tout le cours de l&apos;&Eacute;glise, Jean, dit: J&apos;ai vu une cavale blanche et celui qui la montait portait un arc et sur son front &eacute;tait une couronne; il sortit &ldquo;Vincens&rdquo;, vainqueur. Tu as paru pour vaincre, glorieux Vincent.&rdquo; <br><font color="green">[In the records of the canonisation the allusions are very vague, but here is in the same order of ideas a compliment from Gerson to the master: &ldquo;I honestly believe that you are the angel of the Apocalypse of whom the prophet of all the course of church history, John, tells us: I have seen a white horse and the one who mounted it carried a bow and on his head was a crown; he came out &ldquo;Vincens&rdquo;, winner. You have appeared to win, glorious Vincent.]</font> <small> Matthieu-Maxime Gorce, <a name="STVF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STVF"><cite title="source">Saint Vincent Ferrier</cite></a> (1924) 145-6</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
